horsepower.英释: a unit for measuring the power of an engine, or the power of an engine measured like this

federation.中释: 联合；联邦；联盟；联邦政府
federation.英释: a group of organizations, clubs, or people that have joined together to form a single group

harassment.英释: when someone behaves in an unpleasant or threatening way towards you

remarkable.中释: 卓越的；非凡的；值得注意的
remarkable.英释: unusual or surprising and therefore deserving attention or praise

roundabout.中释: 迂回路线；环状交叉路口
roundabout.英释: a raised circular area where three or more roads join together and which cars must drive around

revelation.中释: 启示；揭露；出乎意料的事；被揭露的真相
revelation.英释: a surprising fact about someone or something that was previously secret and is now made known

sympathize.英释: to feel sorry for someone because you understand their problems

disastrous.中释: 灾难性的；损失惨重的；悲伤的
disastrous.英释: very bad, or ending in failure

accountant.英释: someone whose job is to keep and check financial accounts, calculate taxes etc

capitalism.英释: an economic and political system in which businesses belong mostly to private owners, not to the government

plantation.中释: 适用于种植园或热带、亚热带国家的

pedestrian.英释: someone who is walking, especially along a street or other place used by cars

compatible.中释: 兼容的；能共处的；可并立的
compatible.英释: if two pieces of computer equipment are compatible, they can be used together, especially when they are made by different companies

fellowship.中释: 团体；友谊；奖学金；研究员职位
fellowship.英释: a feeling of friendship resulting from shared interests or experiences

chancellor.中释: 总理（德、奥等的）；（英）大臣；校长（美国某些大学的）；（英）大法官；（美）首席法官

dictionary.英释: a book that gives a list of words in alphabetical order and explains their meanings in the same language, or another language

subjective.英释: a state-ment, report, attitude etc that is subjective is influenced by personal opinion and can therefore be unfair

invaluable.英释: If you describe something as invaluable, you mean that it is extremely useful

descendant.英释: someone who is related to a person who lived a long time ago, or to a family, group of people etc that existed in the past

university.英释: an educational institution at the highest level, where you study for a degree

intimidate.英释: to frighten or threaten someone into making them do what you want

speciality.中释: (specialty) 特色食品; 特产；专业；专门研究；专长
speciality.英释: Someone's speciality is a particular type of work that they do most or do best, or a subject that they know a lot about

simplicity.中释: 简单,简易;朴素;直率,单纯
simplicity.英释: the quality of being simple and not complicated, especially when this is attractive or useful

occurrence.中释: 事件,事故,发生的事情；发生,出现

metropolis.英释: a very large city that is the most important city in a country or area

illustrate.中释: 举例说明,阐明；图解,加插图
illustrate.英释: to make the meaning of something clearer by giving examples

specialize.英释: to limit all or most of your study, business etc to a particular subject or activity

especially.中释: 尤其；特别，格外；专门地，主要地
especially.英释: used to emphasize that something is more important or happens more with one particular thing than with others

difficulty.英释: if you have difficulty doing something, it is difficult for you to do
